Title: OnSTAGE 2026
Description:
Date: 11/02/2026 06:30pm - 09:30pm
Description: Students in Years 10 and 12 Drama will attend OnSTAGE as part of their course work. OnSTAGE is an exhibition of outstanding major works by HSC Drama students in NSW including individual and group performance, and individual projects. One of our own HGHS Drama students will have her work showcased at the event. This is an excellent opportunity for students to see the work by 2025 students ahead of their own HSC year. The organiser has offered a content warning - 'We wish to advise that this performance of OnSTAGE includes coarse language, adult themes, and references to culturally sensitive material, including current political and social issues'.Students will make their own way to the Seymour Centre and arrive by 6:30pm for the roll to be taken by their teacher. The show will start at 7pm and will run for 140 minutes, concluding at approximately 9.20pm. Students will be required to be collected from the Seymour Centre by a parent or caregiver at the conclusion of the show. There is parking under the Seymour Centre, or street parking to allow for this. If there are other pick up arrangements, please write to Ms Mackenzie Carroll with these details prior to the events. 
Participants: 10 & 12 Drama
Venue: Seymour Centre
Faculty: English
Attending Staff: Mackenzie Carroll
Created By: Mackenzie Carroll

Year 11 Legal Aid Presentation (Life Ready)
Description:
Date: 01/05/2026 11:35am - 12:55pm
Description: The Year 11 Life Ready program is part of the mandatory 25-hour course designed to prepare and support senior students as they encounter situations related to their health and safety and future life experiences. As part of the program the following presentation has been selected.Legal Life Skills (T2W2 01/05/2026): Run by Legal Aid NSW, this program provides students with legal skills as they get closer to adulthood and independence. The topic areas will help young people to identify problems that a lawyer can help them with. Topics covered include mobile phone/car contracts, money, fines, workplace rights, renting and credit debt.
